	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what those numbers mean on a normal Tuesday: you scroll and everyone looks happier, prettier, and more included than you. You walk into the cafeteria and wonder where to sit. Your body is changing in ways you didn't choose, and someone made a comment about it. A group chat lights up and you're not in it. You laugh it off, but inside it stings — and you start to wonder if something is wrong with <em>you</em>.</p><p>Nothing is wrong with you. You are right on time, growing exactly the way you were made to. The ache to belong isn't weakness — it's a sign you were made for love. And there is a Father whose love doesn't depend on how you look, who follows you, or whether you got picked. He's been with you the whole time.</p>`}
