	aFatherHeading={`A Father for middle schoolers`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>When you feel left out or not enough, the answer isn't to try harder to be cool, funnier, or different than you are. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a perfect Father in heaven who already calls you His beloved kid.</p><p>Think about that for a second. Before you ever opened an app, before anyone in your school had an opinion about you, God already knew you all the way down — and He <em>likes</em> you. Not the version of you that's trying to impress people. The real you. The one who feels weird sometimes, who messes up, who's still figuring it out. That's the one He calls beloved.</p><p>You don't have to earn a single bit of that love. You can't make Him love you more by getting more follows or better grades, and you can't make Him love you less by having a bad day. His love for you is steady when everything else in middle school feels like it keeps changing. He's your safe place — your true home — and He's not going anywhere.</p>`}
