	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for middle schoolers?`, answer: `Psalm 139:14 (fearfully and wonderfully made), 1 Samuel 16:7 (God looks at the heart, not appearance), Isaiah 41:10 (do not fear, I am with you), Jeremiah 1:5 (known before you were born), Zephaniah 3:17 (He sings over you), 1 Timothy 4:12 (let no one look down on you for being young), and Romans 8:38-39 (nothing can separate you from God's love) all speak straight to middle schoolers. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say when I feel left out or don't fit in?`, answer: `The Bible says your belonging doesn't come from a group of friends — it comes from your Father in heaven. John 1:12 says everyone who receives Jesus is given the right to become a child of God, and Romans 8:38-39 promises nothing can separate you from His love. Even when you feel left out at school, you are never left out of God's family. You can read these verses free, with audio, in the Father's Heart Bible™.` },
		{ question: `Are there Bible verses for anxiety for tweens?`, answer: `Yes. Isaiah 41:10 says, 'Do not fear, for I am with you… I will hold you up,' and Matthew 10:30-31 reminds you that God counts even the hairs on your head and treasures you. When worry hits before a test or a hard day, these verses remind you your Father is right beside you. The Father's Heart Bible™ lets you read or listen to them free on any phone.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about bullying?`, answer: `The Bible says you are deeply valued by God no matter what anyone says about you. 1 Samuel 16:7 says God looks at the heart, not outward appearance, and Matthew 10:31 says you are worth more than many sparrows to your Father. Cruel words don't define you — God's love does. If you're being bullied, tell a trusted adult, and let these verses remind you who you really are. Read them free in the Father's Heart Bible™.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free online Bible with audio for kids and teens?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app to download. Just open fathersheartbible.com/read on any phone or computer and read or hear any book. It's perfect for listening on the bus, before bed, or whenever you need to hear your Father's voice.` },
		{ question: `How can I feel confident in middle school?`, answer: `Real confidence doesn't come from being the most popular or having the best looks — those change. It comes from knowing you are loved no matter what. The Bible says you are fearfully and wonderfully made (Psalm 139:14) and that God set you apart before you were born (Jeremiah 1:5). When your identity rests in your Father's steady love instead of other people's opinions, you can walk into any room secure. Read more in the Father's Heart Bible™.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for middle schoolers?`, answer: `It's the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so instead of a distant 'God,' you meet a loving Dad who already knows and delights in you. For a middle schooler facing comparison, pressure, and change, that reframes everything: you come to the Bible first as a beloved, fully-known child, and learn who you are from the One who made you.` },
